************** G E N E R A L   I N F O R M A T I O N *************2034 1451
                                                                  2034 1451
This evaluated data file is based primarily on a theoretical      2034 1451
analysis with the nuclear model code TALYS [kon04], version 0.56. 2034 1451
The nuclear model parameters of TALYS have been adjusted to       2034 1451
reproduce the existing experimental data. The resulting data file 2034 1451
provides a complete representation of nuclear data needed for     2034 1451
transport, damage, heating, radioactivity, and shielding          2034 1451
applications over the incident neutron energy range from          2034 1451
1.0E-11 to 200 MeV.                                               2034 1451
                                                                  2034 1451
This file is part of a larger collection of isotopic evaluations, 2034 1451
all created by running TALYS with input parameters that do not or 2034 1451
slightly deviate from the default values. The mutual quality of   2034 1451
these isotopic evaluations is thus relatively consistent.         2034 1451
The same set of nuclear models is used and, equally important,    2034 1451
the same ENDF-6 formatting procedures for each isotope. We have   2034 1451
intended to make this evaluation complete in its description of   2034 1451
reaction channels, and use a compact method to store the data.    2034 1451
                                                                  2034 1451
For certain reactions and energy ranges TALYS may not be used.    2034 1451
This is the case when TALYS is not appropriate, such as for the   2034 1451
description of resonances, or when the directly available         2034 1451
experimental data is of better quality, as for e.g. low-energy    2034 1451
total cross sections. In these cases, we have adopted the best    2034 1451
possible data from an existing library, or directly from unfiled  2034 1451
experimental data. All transport data for particles, photons and  2034 1451
residual nuclides are filed using a combination of MF1,2,3,4 and  2034 1451
MF6. This includes cross sections, angular distributions,         2034 1451
double-differential spectra, discrete and continuum photon        2034 1451
production cross sections, and residual production (activation)   2034 1451
cross sections. Moreover, isomeric production data are stored in  2034 1451
MF8 and MF10. This evaluation can thus be used as both transport  2034 1451
and activation library. The data file has been created            2034 1451
automatically using the ENDF-6 format generator TEFAL.            2034 1451
